WEBVTT

01:20.346 --> 01:22.247
Mike.

01:24.585 --> 01:26.985
Hey.
Hey.

01:28.721 --> 01:29.922
Thanks for coming.

01:29.924 --> 01:32.057
Oh, yeah, of course.

01:37.430 --> 01:40.833
I'm just parked
across the street, so...

01:40.835 --> 01:44.169
Okay. I... I was
just gonna hit the...

01:44.171 --> 01:47.806
Yeah, sure.
I'll meet you out front.

01:47.808 --> 01:49.274
Okay.

02:05.658 --> 02:09.761
Janitor.
Anybody here?

03:59.806 --> 04:00.505
Higher!

04:00.507 --> 04:03.408
Higher?
Okay, you asked for it.

04:04.912 --> 04:08.680
Oh, sweetheart.
All right. Come on down.

04:08.682 --> 04:10.882
Pop-Pop's getting tired.
Aw.

04:10.884 --> 04:11.717
Don't "aw" me.

04:11.719 --> 04:15.554
You take a little break...
Little break.

04:16.389 --> 04:18.056
Go on.

04:22.929 --> 04:24.263
A good kid.

04:24.265 --> 04:26.431
Yeah, she is.

04:28.835 --> 04:31.236
So, how do you like it...

04:31.571 --> 04:33.272
Out west?

04:33.373 --> 04:36.541
I like it.
Wide-open spaces.

04:36.543 --> 04:37.776
Yeah.

04:37.778 --> 04:40.212
Mmm.
Different, anyway.

04:40.214 --> 04:42.814
Yeah.

04:43.349 --> 04:45.217
How you doing?

04:45.385 --> 04:48.654
I'm... Yeah, I'm okay,
you know?

04:49.589 --> 04:51.390
Adjusting.

04:52.558 --> 04:54.293
And Kaylee?

04:54.727 --> 04:57.362
Yeah, she's settling in.

04:58.564 --> 05:01.099
She still asks
about him...

05:01.401 --> 05:03.468
"Where is Daddy?"

05:04.337 --> 05:06.204
She just misses him.

05:06.939 --> 05:08.707
Yeah.

05:11.044 --> 05:13.524
How long you in
town for, Mike?

05:13.613 --> 05:15.547
I'm here...

05:15.549 --> 05:17.649
For the duration,
indefinitely.

05:17.651 --> 05:19.484
I'm, uh...

05:20.153 --> 05:21.787
I'm better.

05:21.789 --> 05:23.989
And I'm sorry
it took me so long.

05:23.991 --> 05:28.026
But I'm not like I was.
I'm back. I'm solid.

05:28.561 --> 05:33.198
I want to be here for you,
for Kaylee, for my family.

05:34.133 --> 05:37.669
That's good.
I'm glad to hear
you're better.

05:40.140 --> 05:41.606
What?

05:42.842 --> 05:44.910
What is it, honey?

05:45.478 --> 05:48.380
Mike, I got to ask.
I mean...

05:48.448 --> 05:52.584
I know I just need to
move on from this,

05:52.685 --> 05:55.420
but I keep thinking
about something.

05:55.422 --> 05:56.588
About what?

05:56.590 --> 05:57.590
How, before Matty died,

05:57.591 --> 06:03.562
like, for a few weeks there,
he was... different.

06:03.863 --> 06:05.864
Different how?

06:06.766 --> 06:09.067
Different...
I don't know.

06:09.069 --> 06:10.902
Moody, you know?

06:10.904 --> 06:13.905
He barely ate.
He wasn't sleeping.

06:13.907 --> 06:16.975
He snapped at me about
the stupidest things.

06:16.977 --> 06:19.244
I started to think
something's up
at work or...

06:19.246 --> 06:21.179
Or someone's sick,
something like that,

06:21.181 --> 06:25.183
but he wouldn't talk to me.
He clammed right up.

06:25.185 --> 06:28.787
Cops aren't real touchy-feely.
You know that.

06:29.422 --> 06:31.256
No.

06:31.258 --> 06:33.058
They're not. No.

06:33.060 --> 06:37.796
But this wasn't
the normal "tough guys
don't cry" crap.

06:37.798 --> 06:40.132
This was more.
I mean...

06:40.833 --> 06:41.500
Did you notice?

06:41.502 --> 06:44.503
I mean, did you feel
anything like that
from him?

06:44.505 --> 06:48.340
I don't...
As far as I remember,
he seemed okay.

06:48.342 --> 06:50.142
He seemed okay to me.

06:50.144 --> 06:53.178
Well, I started to think...
I'm...

06:53.180 --> 06:56.181
I don't know.
I didn't know what to think.

06:57.183 --> 06:58.316
But then...

06:58.318 --> 07:00.485
Three days or four...
I don't remember,

07:00.487 --> 07:03.054
but before he died,
there was this phone call.

07:03.056 --> 07:06.992
2:30 in the morning,
I wake up,
and Matty's not in bed.

07:06.994 --> 07:09.127
And I hear him.
He's talking downstairs.

07:09.129 --> 07:15.167
So... I go to listen
on the stairs,
where he couldn't see.

07:15.768 --> 07:17.836
He gets intense.

07:18.037 --> 07:19.504
Like, he'd be screaming

07:19.506 --> 07:22.073
if he wasn't whispering,
you know?

07:22.075 --> 07:25.143
Matty didn't get worked up.
He'd let things go.

07:25.145 --> 07:29.114
But... But this...
I mean, he was angry.

07:29.116 --> 07:31.383
He was really angry.

07:31.851 --> 07:33.084
What was he saying?

07:33.086 --> 07:37.155
I couldn't make it out.
It was something about...

07:37.957 --> 07:40.859
I don't know.
I couldn't hear it.

07:42.029 --> 07:43.728
But the next morning,
I called him out,

07:43.730 --> 07:46.665
"What the hell was that about?
What's going on?"

07:46.667 --> 07:49.134
And he wouldn't
talk to me.

07:49.669 --> 07:52.103
But I think...

07:52.672 --> 07:55.674
I think he was
talking to you.

07:56.709 --> 07:59.744
Me?
I mean, who else?

08:01.013 --> 08:02.347
Huh?

08:02.515 --> 08:06.017
For one hot second,
I thought maybe
he was catting around...

08:06.019 --> 08:07.385
No, he wouldn't do that.

08:07.387 --> 08:10.088
No, I know.
I know that. But you...

08:10.090 --> 08:12.657
He knew he could call you
anytime he had a problem.

08:12.659 --> 08:14.893
You were thick as thieves,
the two of you.

08:14.895 --> 08:16.928
And there was
something in his voice.

08:16.930 --> 08:20.298
It was...
How he was talking.

08:20.600 --> 08:22.767
It makes me think
it was you.

08:22.769 --> 08:24.903
Stace,
I don't think it was.

08:24.905 --> 08:29.274
I can't recall
any late-night
heart-to-hearts with him,

08:29.276 --> 08:31.009
not around then.

08:31.011 --> 08:33.879
Maybe it was a C.I.
or a case.

08:34.947 --> 08:36.248
Listen.

08:36.250 --> 08:39.217
I know what you're doing,
replaying it over and over,

08:39.219 --> 08:42.053
thinking, "If I'd noticed
this or changed that,

08:42.055 --> 08:44.422
"maybe I could have
done something."

08:44.424 --> 08:48.460
You don't think I haven't had
those thoughts? I do.

08:49.730 --> 08:51.630
Every day.

08:52.031 --> 08:55.667
You got to quit beating
yourself up like this.

08:58.204 --> 09:00.872
Matty's gone.

09:01.173 --> 09:04.442
That's really
all there is to it.

09:09.782 --> 09:11.383
Yeah.

09:13.352 --> 09:15.921
I guess that's that.

09:20.026 --> 09:21.893
It's getting on.
I got to...

09:21.895 --> 09:26.565
Get Kaylee her dinner
and put her to bed.

09:28.067 --> 09:29.701
Uh, yeah.

09:32.038 --> 09:33.738
Okay.

09:34.974 --> 09:36.541
Well, if you want me
to drop by

09:36.543 --> 09:39.444
and keep an eye on her,
I...

09:39.912 --> 09:41.713
I want to help.

09:52.091 --> 09:54.225
See you around.

10:26.960 --> 10:29.127
Where to?

10:30.363 --> 10:32.330
"Francisco."

10:32.531 --> 10:33.398
Yeah.

10:33.400 --> 10:34.966
You know this town?

10:34.968 --> 10:36.568
Yeah, sure.

10:36.570 --> 10:38.269
How well?

10:39.105 --> 10:43.108
You sew this up yourself?

10:43.943 --> 10:46.044
Not bad.

10:46.245 --> 10:47.679
Bet there's
a story there.

10:47.681 --> 10:50.315
Isn't there always?
Yeah.

10:50.317 --> 10:53.284
All right.
Little sting here.

10:53.919 --> 10:57.389
Okay.
That ought to do it.

10:58.090 --> 10:59.157
Now...

10:59.159 --> 11:01.960
You're gonna want to
take it easy.

11:02.128 --> 11:03.495
Keep it clean.

11:03.497 --> 11:05.664
Keep it dry.
Let it heal.

11:05.666 --> 11:09.467
There's a Walgreens
a couple blocks over
on Louisiana.

11:09.469 --> 11:12.037
Maybe go get
yourself a sling.

11:12.039 --> 11:13.371
You don't have one?

11:13.373 --> 11:14.673
Sorry.

11:14.675 --> 11:16.775
Got a cone you can put
around your neck.

11:16.777 --> 11:18.276
Yeah.

11:18.278 --> 11:20.779
It's about the same,
right?

11:21.147 --> 11:23.682
So, it's gonna be $500?

11:23.684 --> 11:24.349
$500.

11:24.351 --> 11:29.154
I can, uh, throw some
pills in for the pain.

11:29.690 --> 11:31.423
This stuff's
essentially Vicodin.

11:31.425 --> 11:34.392
I can give it to you
for $25 a pill...

11:34.394 --> 11:36.094
Maybe drop the price
to $15

11:36.096 --> 11:39.130
for something a little
less human-centric.

11:39.132 --> 11:41.666
I'm an aspirin man.

11:41.668 --> 11:45.503
Tell you what.
Take a couple
on the house.

11:45.871 --> 11:48.440
In case you
change your mind.

11:50.776 --> 11:52.444
You new in town?

11:52.446 --> 11:53.945
Yeah.

11:54.447 --> 11:57.282
Passing through
or sticking around?

11:57.950 --> 11:59.117
Why?

11:59.119 --> 11:59.751
No reason.

11:59.753 --> 12:05.457
It's just,
if you're relocating to
the Land of Enchantment,

12:05.925 --> 12:07.859
I know people.

12:08.060 --> 12:09.694
I could get you
some work.

12:09.696 --> 12:13.531
I am not looking
for that kind of work,

12:13.833 --> 12:15.467
but...

12:16.235 --> 12:18.837
Thanks.

12:22.007 --> 12:24.342
Don't know why
it has to be this way.

12:24.344 --> 12:25.243
Could have been friendly.

12:25.245 --> 12:27.278
Could have talked
in your house.

12:27.280 --> 12:30.348
You really want
the formal treatment?

12:30.350 --> 12:32.117
Lawyer.

12:32.119 --> 12:33.351
Come on, Mike.

12:33.353 --> 12:34.819
It's just
a couple of questions.

12:34.821 --> 12:38.056
Uh, ain't nothing
but a thing.

12:38.290 --> 12:39.724
Lawyer.

12:39.726 --> 12:41.359
You're not under arrest.

12:41.361 --> 12:43.361
Okay, did anybody here
say "arrest"? No.

12:43.363 --> 12:45.029
You want to walk, walk.

12:45.031 --> 12:45.830
I got to say, I, uh,

12:45.832 --> 12:50.802
expected more
cooperation from you
on this, cop to cop.

12:52.304 --> 12:53.972
Lawyer.

13:02.047 --> 13:03.715
Fine.

13:03.783 --> 13:05.650
What lawyer?

13:12.992 --> 13:16.494
Ehrmantraut.
Who's got him and where?

13:16.496 --> 13:18.363
That way.

13:18.798 --> 13:20.598
Hey, fellas.
How you doing?

13:20.600 --> 13:24.035
James McGill.
Here to see my client.

13:25.437 --> 13:26.004
What?

13:26.006 --> 13:27.472
You look like Matlock.
Uh, no.

13:27.474 --> 13:32.143
I look like
a young Paul Newman
dressed as Matlock.

13:32.511 --> 13:34.312
Where's my guy?

13:36.349 --> 13:38.516
Say hello to Barney Fife.

13:38.518 --> 13:41.853
Wrong show,
but thanks for playing.

13:45.492 --> 13:46.191
So, what happened?

13:46.193 --> 13:49.694
The Mayor didn't give you
enough stickers?

13:51.397 --> 13:53.965
You want to tell me
what we're doing here?

13:53.967 --> 13:55.033
Oh, here's your coffee.

13:55.035 --> 13:58.136
Uh, hope it's good
to the last drop,

13:58.138 --> 14:01.239
'cause I'm billing you
the full hour for it.

14:01.241 --> 14:02.540
That's for you.

14:02.542 --> 14:05.210
Oh. That's very
thoughtful.

14:07.112 --> 14:08.680
You serious?

14:08.682 --> 14:09.781
Why did you have me
bring it to you?

14:09.783 --> 14:11.482
All right,
here's what's gonna happen.

14:11.484 --> 14:14.419
Those two cops out there
are from Philadelphia.

14:14.421 --> 14:16.020
They've come
a long way to see me.

14:16.022 --> 14:19.190
When they come in here,
we're all gonna have
a little chat.

14:19.192 --> 14:19.858
And when it's over,

14:19.860 --> 14:22.026
the young one,
who's been writing
in his little notebook,

14:22.028 --> 14:24.596
he's gonna take it
and put it in his jacket.

14:24.598 --> 14:25.763
And when he does that,

14:25.765 --> 14:29.801
I want you to
take that coffee
and spill it on him.

14:30.069 --> 14:32.237
Little accident,
that's all.

14:32.239 --> 14:34.672
And why, pray tell,
would I do that?

14:34.674 --> 14:35.440
Because I'm asking you to.

14:35.442 --> 14:36.875
It's the only reason
you're here.

14:36.877 --> 14:40.011
So I'm here because
you want me to assault
a police officer.

14:40.013 --> 14:44.649
I am asking you to
take a few ounces
of lukewarm coffee

14:44.651 --> 14:45.383
and spill it on him.

14:45.385 --> 14:49.387
I doubt that satisfies
the definition
of "assault,"

14:49.389 --> 14:52.423
but, hey,
you're the lawyer.

14:52.425 --> 14:55.093
Right.
How silly of me.

14:55.095 --> 14:57.128
All you want is for me
to aid and abet

14:57.130 --> 14:58.363
you ripping off
that guy's notepad,

14:58.365 --> 15:00.398
'cause that's what
you're doing here, right?

15:00.400 --> 15:02.567
Huh? What,
are you nuts?

15:02.569 --> 15:03.334
You can't be serious.

15:03.336 --> 15:06.604
Hey, I hate to
remind you of this,
but you owe me one.

15:06.606 --> 15:09.507
The assist I gave you
with the missing persons
problem?

15:09.509 --> 15:11.109
One good turn
and so forth?

15:11.111 --> 15:14.679
You want a good turn?
Here's your good turn,
okay?

15:14.681 --> 15:15.413
I'm gonna behave

15:15.415 --> 15:19.417
like an honest-to-God,
law-abiding,
licensed attorney,

15:19.419 --> 15:20.752
'cause, clearly,
you need one

15:20.754 --> 15:22.186
with whatever the hell
is going on here.

15:22.188 --> 15:23.521
Now, those two jokers
out in the hallway...

15:23.523 --> 15:26.291
I'm gonna make sure
they dot their I's
and cross their T's...

15:26.293 --> 15:29.260
Everything square
and above board.

15:29.262 --> 15:30.094
That's what I'm gonna do,

15:30.096 --> 15:32.430
and you're gonna
be happy as hell
that I'm here.

15:32.432 --> 15:37.635
But this little
Juan Valdez
bump-and-dump... No.

15:37.770 --> 15:39.804
Not gonna happen.

15:39.806 --> 15:44.075
Hey, gentlemen,
we're prepared to
indulge you.

15:45.679 --> 15:50.315
Detective Escalara
will be sitting in with us,
as per APD policy.

15:50.317 --> 15:52.050
Okay with you, right?

15:52.052 --> 15:53.885
Fine with me.

15:53.887 --> 15:54.786
Okay.

15:54.788 --> 15:57.922
You got your lawyer, Mike.
Can we talk already?

15:58.791 --> 16:00.058
Great.
So, like we said,

16:00.060 --> 16:02.460
we're here
looking into this
Hoffman and Fensky thing.

16:02.462 --> 16:05.563
Yeah, and whatever
you can tell us...
Anything at all.

16:05.565 --> 16:07.665
Uh, hold on.
Hold on.

16:07.833 --> 16:09.901
"Hoffman. Fensky."

16:09.903 --> 16:11.602
Fill me in.

16:11.604 --> 16:14.038
Assume I know
absolutely nothing

16:14.040 --> 16:15.340
about my client here,
all right?

16:15.342 --> 16:16.741
Start at the beginning.
Jesus. Seriously?

16:16.743 --> 16:20.378
Look, don't let
Mr. Ehrmantraut's
dancing eyes

16:20.380 --> 16:23.147
and bubbly,
bon vivant personality
fool you.

16:23.149 --> 16:27.251
He's actually,
believe it or not,
somewhat taciturn.

16:27.253 --> 16:31.089
Shall I fan you gently,
so you don't go into shock?

16:31.091 --> 16:32.757
Start at the beginning,
okay?

16:32.759 --> 16:34.125
We're talking
Book of Genesis.

16:34.127 --> 16:37.628
Okay, Mr. McGill,
as you probably gathered,

16:37.630 --> 16:38.997
we...
Detective Sanders and I

16:38.999 --> 16:41.332
work for the Philadelphia
Police Department,

16:41.334 --> 16:43.801
as did Mr. Ehrmantraut
for nearly 30 years.

16:43.803 --> 16:46.637
Philadelphia?
Go, Eagles.

16:46.639 --> 16:48.673
Mr. Ehrmantraut
had a son, Matt.

16:48.675 --> 16:50.074
He, too,
was with Philly PD.

16:50.076 --> 16:53.378
He was a rookie officer
with about two years
on the job.

16:53.380 --> 16:56.614
He was a good cop.
Yes, he was.

16:56.616 --> 16:57.982
About nine months ago,
he responded

16:57.984 --> 17:01.152
to a shots-fired call
in some Westside rattrap.

17:01.154 --> 17:03.688
Matt went in
with his partner,
Officer Troy Hoffman.

17:03.690 --> 17:07.258
They had
Sergeant Jack Fensky
backing them up.

17:07.260 --> 17:09.827
Unfortunately,
things got out of hand.

17:09.829 --> 17:11.062
The three of them
were ambushed,

17:11.064 --> 17:13.498
and, uh,
Matt didn't make it out.

17:13.500 --> 17:15.566
Hoffman and Fensky
returned fire,

17:15.568 --> 17:16.334
but the shooter got away.

17:16.336 --> 17:19.871
We chased a few leads,
shook up the usual suspects...

17:19.873 --> 17:21.606
Came up short.

17:22.841 --> 17:25.676
I'm very sorry
to hear it.

17:25.678 --> 17:27.478
Anyways,
we kept beating the bushes,

17:27.480 --> 17:30.515
kept coming up dry
until three months ago.

17:30.517 --> 17:32.950
That's when Hoffman and Fensky
both turned up dead

17:32.952 --> 17:34.685
in a vacant lot
out in Nicetown.

17:34.687 --> 17:36.788
Again, an ambush of some kind,
it looks like.

17:36.790 --> 17:40.658
And with whoever killed
Matt out there in the wind,
we're thinking...

17:40.660 --> 17:41.626
Well, it's our
operating theory

17:41.628 --> 17:44.896
that Hoffman and Fensky
were mixed up in something,

17:44.898 --> 17:46.731
some bad business,

17:46.733 --> 17:48.299
and maybe that
got Matt killed.

17:48.301 --> 17:50.068
Yeah, sorry. I got to do
my lawyer thing here.

17:50.070 --> 17:53.104
Uh, what does my
client have to do
with any of this?

17:53.106 --> 17:56.541
Uh, Mike,
this is a Hail Mary.

17:56.642 --> 17:57.742
Uh, beyond that.

17:57.744 --> 18:00.678
I mean, if we had
any hard evidence or leads,

18:00.680 --> 18:01.779
we wouldn't be out here.

18:01.781 --> 18:03.381
Now, there's anything
you can tell us

18:03.383 --> 18:06.317
about what
Hoffman and Fensky
were into?

18:06.319 --> 18:07.251
Yeah, help us out, Mike.

18:07.253 --> 18:10.388
Help us catch
the bastard who
killed Matty.

18:12.991 --> 18:14.892
I don't know much
about Hoffman and Fensky.

18:14.894 --> 18:18.696
They were Matt's people.
I'd see them around
sometimes.

18:18.698 --> 18:21.632
I saw them in a bar
the night they died.

18:21.634 --> 18:22.567
It was McClure's,

18:22.569 --> 18:25.970
maybe the Red Dog...
Probably McClure's.

18:26.839 --> 18:28.272
Were they drinking
with anyone?

18:28.274 --> 18:29.807
It's a cop bar.
They were drinking
with everyone.

18:29.809 --> 18:32.477
Yeah, but did you
see them with anyone
in particular?

18:32.479 --> 18:35.513
I couldn't tell you.
I was...

18:36.315 --> 18:37.615
You know how I was.

18:37.617 --> 18:39.317
How you doing
these days?

18:39.319 --> 18:42.220
Feeling like I
crawled out from
the bottom of a bottle

18:42.222 --> 18:44.922
and working hard
to stay there.

18:44.924 --> 18:45.924
Although I've got to say,

18:45.925 --> 18:50.828
doesn't help much,
dredging up the past
like this.

18:51.697 --> 18:52.930
Let me ask you,

18:52.932 --> 18:55.133
uh, when did you come
out here to Albuquerque?

18:55.135 --> 18:57.869
It couldn't have been, uh,
too much later.

18:57.871 --> 18:59.504
I think it was
the very next day.

18:59.506 --> 19:03.608
Yeah? The day after
Hoffman and Fensky
died, huh?

19:03.610 --> 19:07.311
You didn't think
to, uh, stick around
once you heard the news?

19:07.313 --> 19:09.046
I don't think
I heard the news

19:09.048 --> 19:10.815
till I was west
of Kansas City.

19:10.817 --> 19:11.582
Still, you, uh...

19:11.584 --> 19:13.518
You didn't come back
for the funerals, correct?

19:13.520 --> 19:14.952
Even though Hoffman
was Matt's partner?

19:14.954 --> 19:19.123
Uh, do you remember anything
about that night at the bar?

19:19.125 --> 19:22.560
Uh, did you talk to
Hoffman or Fensky
at all?

19:22.562 --> 19:25.129
Sorry. I got nothing.
They weren't my people.

19:26.498 --> 19:28.332
I'm sorry you guys
took a flier on me.

19:28.334 --> 19:30.568
I wish it'd have
paid off.

19:30.570 --> 19:31.936
That it?

19:31.938 --> 19:33.704
We done here?

19:33.706 --> 19:35.740
We're done here, yeah.

19:35.807 --> 19:37.642
Hey, that wasn't
so hard, huh?

19:37.644 --> 19:38.709
Thanks, Mike.
Yeah.

19:38.711 --> 19:40.811
Listen, we're probably
gonna kick around
for another couple of days,

19:40.813 --> 19:42.780
in case you think of
something, all right?

19:42.782 --> 19:46.250
You know, I've never been
out west before.

19:47.787 --> 19:48.986
Oh, hey.

19:48.988 --> 19:50.054
Oh!
Oh, shit!

19:50.056 --> 19:51.088
Jesus. Sorry. Sorry.
Come on!

19:51.090 --> 19:53.257
Here. I can get
most of it.
You got any paper towels?

19:53.259 --> 19:54.959
You know what?
Hey, hey.
I... I got it.

19:54.961 --> 19:56.861
I got it. Thank you.
Sorry.

20:16.249 --> 20:16.948
Oh, for the love of...

20:16.950 --> 20:21.085
You got to do that
right here,
right in front of me?

20:21.853 --> 20:22.653
What's so important
in there

20:22.655 --> 20:26.424
that we had to
pull that third-rate
Marx Brothers routine?

20:26.758 --> 20:28.359
You really want to know?

20:28.361 --> 20:31.128
And risk getting a piece
of an obstruction rap?

20:31.130 --> 20:32.930
No, thank you.

20:33.098 --> 20:36.167
Anything else
you want to ask?

20:38.403 --> 20:40.304
How did you know?

20:40.572 --> 20:42.440
Know what?

20:42.442 --> 20:45.443
That... That I would
do that, that...

20:46.112 --> 20:51.983
How did you know
that I would, uh,
spill that coffee?

20:54.487 --> 20:55.553
What the hell's that?

20:55.555 --> 20:59.624
What's
supposed to mean, huh?

21:00.592 --> 21:03.427
Okay, great.
You're the strong,
silent type.

21:03.429 --> 21:04.929
Hooray for you.

21:04.931 --> 21:05.931
But in case
you missed it,

21:05.932 --> 21:08.132
your friends from
Philly back there?

21:08.134 --> 21:10.968
They think you
killed two cops.

21:13.105 --> 21:15.239
Yep.

22:10.495 --> 22:12.229
Yeah, it's me.

22:12.564 --> 22:14.498
We need to talk.

22:21.039 --> 22:22.973
You call the cops?

22:23.375 --> 22:23.974
What?

22:23.976 --> 22:26.744
Philadelphia PD.
Did you call them?

22:26.746 --> 22:27.746
Yeah, I did.
Why?

22:27.747 --> 22:31.082
Well, I told them
I heard about
Hoffman and Fensky and...

22:31.084 --> 22:31.849
And what?

22:31.851 --> 22:33.951
And you don't think
it's strange?

22:33.953 --> 22:36.420
First Matt,
then not six months later,

22:36.422 --> 22:37.988
his partner
and his sergeant?

22:37.990 --> 22:40.891
Yeah, I called them
to help catch
Matty's killer.

22:40.893 --> 22:42.960
Mike, what if
the same person,
if the...

22:42.962 --> 22:45.796
What if the piece of
shit who got Matty
got them too?

22:45.798 --> 22:48.399
And what exactly
did you tell them?

22:48.401 --> 22:50.534
I told them...
You tell them
Matt was dirty?

22:50.536 --> 22:51.902
Is that what
you told them?
I...

22:51.904 --> 22:53.270
How could you
possibly think that?

22:53.272 --> 22:55.840
That's your husband,
the father of your child.

22:55.842 --> 22:57.942
I didn't say that. I...

22:57.944 --> 22:59.176
I told them I found money.

22:59.178 --> 23:01.579
After Kaylee and I
moved here,
when I was unpacking,

23:01.581 --> 23:03.614
it was in the lining
of an old suitcase.

23:03.616 --> 23:07.385
Matt must have
tucked it away in there,
'cause this was cash...

23:07.387 --> 23:10.955
$5,000, $6,000
from God knows where.

23:10.957 --> 23:12.990
I mean, we were basically
paycheck to paycheck.

23:12.992 --> 23:14.959
Where the hell
did he get it?

23:14.961 --> 23:15.893
Why didn't you ask me?

23:15.895 --> 23:18.429
Why didn't
you come to me?

23:18.431 --> 23:19.130
I couldn't.

23:19.132 --> 23:21.031
I knew what
it would do to you.

23:21.033 --> 23:24.135
First, he's murdered,
and then for you to think...

23:24.137 --> 23:26.070
It would have
burned you to the ground.

23:26.072 --> 23:28.873
There would be
nothing left.

23:28.875 --> 23:30.207
And you wouldn't
talk to me.

23:30.209 --> 23:33.144
Every night,
you were drinking
yourself unconscious,

23:33.146 --> 23:36.313
like you were
the only one
who lost him.

23:36.315 --> 23:38.482
Look, I don't care.
He was dirty,
he was clean...

23:38.484 --> 23:39.116
I don't care.

23:39.118 --> 23:41.018
All I want is for
whoever killed Matty

23:41.020 --> 23:42.486
to rot in a cell for
the rest of their life,

23:42.488 --> 23:46.190
and then I want
whatever's left of them
just dumped in the trash.

23:46.192 --> 23:46.791
That's what I want.

23:46.793 --> 23:49.126
I don't care
where it leads,
what it uncovers.

23:49.128 --> 23:52.096
I mean,
what difference
would it make

23:52.098 --> 23:54.932
if he was... anything?

23:55.233 --> 23:56.400
I'd still love him.

23:56.402 --> 23:58.836
I'd still miss him.
He'd still be gone.

23:58.838 --> 24:00.504
Matt wasn't dirty.

24:00.506 --> 24:02.473
Well, so be
straight with me!

24:02.475 --> 24:04.008
Right now.
This is it, Mike.

24:04.010 --> 24:07.478
What was that phone call
before he died?

24:07.480 --> 24:08.112
Don't bullshit me.

24:08.114 --> 24:11.649
That was between
me and my son.

24:11.950 --> 24:14.285
So you're admitting
it was you.

24:14.287 --> 24:15.052
He wasn't dirty!

24:15.054 --> 24:20.057
Goddamn you!
You get that
through your head!

24:20.059 --> 24:23.461
My son wasn't dirty!

24:43.982 --> 24:45.683
<i>♪ Oh, it came out of the sky</i>

24:45.685 --> 24:50.888
<i>♪ Landed just a little
south of Moline</i>

24:50.890 --> 24:52.756
<i>♪ Jody fell out
of his tractor</i>

24:52.758 --> 24:56.393
<i>♪ Couldn't believe
what he'd seen</i>

24:56.962 --> 25:02.466
<i>♪ Laid on the ground, a-shook,
fearing for his life</i>

25:02.968 --> 25:05.336
<i>♪ Then he ran
all the way to town</i>

25:05.338 --> 25:09.573
<i>♪ Screaming,
"It came out of the sky!"</i>

25:09.575 --> 25:10.975
<i>♪ Well, a crowd
gathered 'round</i>

25:10.977 --> 25:15.579
<i>♪ And a scientist said
it was marsh gas</i>

25:15.581 --> 25:21.719
<i>♪ Spiro came</i>
<i>and made a speech</i>
<i>about raising the mars tax</i>

25:22.954 --> 25:26.390
<i>♪ The Vatican said,
"Woe, the Lord has come"</i>

25:26.392 --> 25:28.926
<i>♪ Hollywood rushed out
an epic film</i>

25:28.928 --> 25:34.665
<i>♪ Ronnie the popular
said it was a communist plot</i>

25:34.667 --> 25:37.601
<i>♪ Whoa</i>

26:00.225 --> 26:06.964
<i>♪ Oh, the newspapers</i>
<i>came and made Jody</i>
<i>a national hero ♪</i>

26:55.380 --> 26:59.149
<i>♪ And my mind goes back
to a girl I left</i>

26:59.151 --> 27:03.554
<i>♪ Long years ago who told me</i>

27:03.556 --> 27:05.322
<i>♪ Just hold on loosely</i>

27:07.225 --> 27:08.993
<i>♪ But don't let go</i>

27:08.995 --> 27:11.695
<i>♪ If you cling too tightly</i>

27:11.697 --> 27:14.698
Just let him cry it
all out, okay?

27:16.035 --> 27:16.867
Hey, Mikey.

27:16.869 --> 27:17.968
Young Hoffman.
Mikey boy.

27:17.970 --> 27:20.871
What's going on,
my brothers?
How you doing?

27:20.873 --> 27:22.172
Brothers, huh?

27:22.174 --> 27:24.875
Good to see you, too.
It's been a minute.

27:24.877 --> 27:27.011
Yeah.

27:27.780 --> 27:31.115
I know.
I know it was you.

27:35.421 --> 27:40.557
<i>♪ Don't let your heart
get in the way</i>

27:42.027 --> 27:44.995
<i>♪ You see it all around you</i>

27:45.697 --> 27:49.099
<i>♪ Good loving gone bad</i>

27:49.101 --> 27:53.070
<i>♪ And usually it's too late
when you</i>

27:53.072 --> 27:55.506
<i>♪ Realize what you had ♪</i>

27:59.811 --> 28:01.979
Closing time, Mikey.

28:01.981 --> 28:02.946
Yeah?

28:02.948 --> 28:05.249
Yeah, yeah, yeah, okay.

28:05.251 --> 28:07.484
Hey, how about I
give you a lift home?

28:07.486 --> 28:09.353
Mmm...

28:10.455 --> 28:11.622
I'm fine.

28:11.624 --> 28:13.691
No, I can't let you drive.
Get you a cab?

28:13.693 --> 28:16.527
No, I'm good.
I'm good.

28:16.529 --> 28:18.062
Don't worry.

28:18.064 --> 28:22.032
Anyway, I sold my car,
so I'm walking.

28:22.267 --> 28:24.034
Thank you.

28:24.869 --> 28:28.472
Albuquerque,
New Mexico.

28:29.541 --> 28:32.443
You ever been?
Nope.

28:32.445 --> 28:34.044
Well...

28:35.113 --> 28:37.147
That's where I'm headed.

28:37.149 --> 28:38.982
Tarantulas, they got.

28:38.984 --> 28:40.784
That's a big minus
in my book.

28:40.786 --> 28:45.989
Well,
I will be on the lookout.

28:46.524 --> 28:48.592
You take care,
my friend.

28:48.594 --> 28:50.360
Take care.

29:23.929 --> 29:25.829
Hey, Mike.

29:26.731 --> 29:28.265
Mikey.

29:32.137 --> 29:34.104
You want a ride?

29:34.739 --> 29:36.607
I'll walk it.

29:37.809 --> 29:39.743
Pull over here.

29:46.117 --> 29:47.518
What are you
doing out here?

29:47.520 --> 29:48.786
Come on.
Let us drive you.

29:48.788 --> 29:51.155
It's colder than
my ex-wife's tit out here.

29:51.157 --> 29:53.257
Come on. Come on.

29:53.259 --> 29:53.824
I'm walking.

29:53.826 --> 29:54.992
Come on. Don't...
Don't be an ass.

29:54.994 --> 29:57.227
Come on.
Let us take you home.
Get in the car already.

29:57.229 --> 29:58.028
It's cold out here.

29:58.030 --> 30:00.564
What?
Come on, Mike.
Come on.

30:00.566 --> 30:03.167
Come on.

30:04.035 --> 30:05.969
Okay. Easy.

30:06.806 --> 30:09.239
We're gonna have you
home in no time.

30:09.774 --> 30:11.775
Oh, God.

30:12.177 --> 30:15.245
Hey.
What are you doing?

30:15.247 --> 30:19.650
Hey. Give me that.
That's mine.

30:20.485 --> 30:21.051
Later.

30:21.053 --> 30:25.289
We don't want you
to shoot your foot off,
now, do we?

30:40.638 --> 30:43.140
Hey, Mikey.
What?

30:43.142 --> 30:45.209
Mikey, you with us?

30:45.211 --> 30:46.677
Why?

30:46.679 --> 30:49.413
You really tied one
on good back there,
buddy.

30:49.415 --> 30:50.180
Shit, yeah, he did.

30:50.182 --> 30:53.851
Put it away
like they were fixing
to bring back Prohibition.

30:55.454 --> 30:56.820
Hey. Hey,
back at McClure's,

30:56.822 --> 30:58.956
you were talking
out your ass, hmm?

30:58.958 --> 31:01.725
"I know it was you."

31:01.727 --> 31:03.727
What's that
supposed to mean, huh?

31:03.729 --> 31:05.362
You think you know what?

31:05.364 --> 31:08.098
You got
something you want to
get off your chest?

31:08.100 --> 31:10.381
Something you
want to say to us?

31:11.636 --> 31:13.837
You killed him.

31:15.173 --> 31:17.374
You killed Matty.

31:18.109 --> 31:21.578
And you killed him
for nothing.

31:22.413 --> 31:24.681
You killed him
because you were scared

31:24.683 --> 31:28.185
of what you
thought he might do.

31:28.386 --> 31:31.755
You got him
in that crack house...

31:32.957 --> 31:35.325
And you staged it...

31:36.694 --> 31:40.330
Made it look like
a junkie with a gun.

31:48.072 --> 31:50.207
But it was you.

31:51.976 --> 31:54.845
And I know it was you.

31:59.183 --> 32:01.919
And I'm gonna prove it.

32:34.018 --> 32:37.287
Help me get him
out of the car.

32:52.270 --> 32:53.303
What?

32:53.305 --> 32:56.840
Come on.
There you go.
Watch your head.

32:58.677 --> 33:00.477
All right,
come on, Mike, huh?

33:00.479 --> 33:02.779
One, two, one, two,
buddy.

33:04.782 --> 33:06.850
Now, you wait there
one second.

33:06.852 --> 33:10.721
We're gonna work this
whole thing out,
okay, Mikey?

33:12.790 --> 33:13.924
What do we do now?

33:13.926 --> 33:16.727
Hey. Grief,
it's a bitch.

33:18.162 --> 33:21.331
He couldn't live with it...
Matt dying the way he did.

33:21.333 --> 33:22.432
It's too much
for the old man.

33:22.434 --> 33:24.468
So Mikey here decided
to eat his gun.

33:24.470 --> 33:28.372
It's tragic,
but anyone could
see this coming, hmm?

33:28.374 --> 33:30.307
He's drinking
himself to death.

33:30.309 --> 33:33.176
We're doing him
a favor.

33:33.178 --> 33:34.277
Smart.

33:34.279 --> 33:37.581
That's what I would
have done if I were you.
Whoa.

34:26.230 --> 34:28.065
Mike, I...

35:15.379 --> 35:20.517
<i>You let some things slide
and you look the other way.</i>

35:20.952 --> 35:21.685
<i>You bust a drug dealer</i>

35:21.687 --> 35:26.089
<i>that has more cash</i>
<i>than you'll ever</i>
<i>earn in a lifetime.</i>

35:26.091 --> 35:30.327
<i>Some of it</i>
<i>doesn't make it</i>
<i>back into evidence.</i>

35:30.329 --> 35:31.928
<i>So what?</i>

35:31.930 --> 35:35.699
<i>You took a taste.
So did everyone else.</i>

35:36.000 --> 35:40.170
<i>That's how you knew
you were safe.</i>

35:42.340 --> 35:44.574
<i>It's like killing Caesar...</i>

35:44.909 --> 35:47.244
<i>Everyone's guilty.</i>

35:48.779 --> 35:51.181
<i>Matt wasn't dirty.</i>

35:52.416 --> 35:54.017
I was.

35:54.352 --> 35:57.721
Everyone was
in that precinct.

35:58.022 --> 36:00.023
That's how it worked.

36:00.025 --> 36:04.561
You turn in your buddy,
you're screwing yourself.

36:05.663 --> 36:09.533
You go along
to get along.

36:11.736 --> 36:14.037
And you went along.

36:19.577 --> 36:20.977
I did.

36:22.547 --> 36:24.014
Yeah.

36:24.782 --> 36:26.416
I did.

36:26.984 --> 36:31.721
Okay.
But you said Matt didn't.

36:32.423 --> 36:33.790
No.

36:34.225 --> 36:36.092
Not Matt.

36:36.861 --> 36:40.096
Fensky got to
Hoffman early.

36:40.498 --> 36:43.733
Kickbacks from
some gang or another...

36:43.735 --> 36:45.535
Protection, basically.

36:45.537 --> 36:48.738
And Hoffman went to Matty
and offered to cut him in.

36:48.740 --> 36:51.474
Only fair, right?
They were partners.

36:53.778 --> 36:57.113
And Matt did
what you would think...

36:57.848 --> 37:00.016
He agonized.

37:00.284 --> 37:05.121
And then he came to me,
wanted to go to the IA,

37:05.123 --> 37:06.389
do the right thing,
shut 'em down.

37:06.391 --> 37:07.591
Oh, my God.
And you let him?

37:07.593 --> 37:11.294
That's why he got killed?
'Cause he was gonna
turn on those guys?

37:11.296 --> 37:13.430
No. No.

37:15.633 --> 37:17.567
I told him...

37:19.670 --> 37:23.206
You know what
a cop fears most?

37:23.708 --> 37:27.010
More than getting shot,
more than anything?

37:28.112 --> 37:29.412
Prison.

37:29.414 --> 37:33.149
Getting locked up
with everybody
you put away.

37:33.618 --> 37:35.919
You threaten a cop
with that,

37:35.921 --> 37:37.787
you make him dangerous,

37:37.789 --> 37:40.290
and that's
what I told him.

37:40.391 --> 37:42.859
I talked sense.

37:43.628 --> 37:46.429
No one
was getting hurt.

37:46.530 --> 37:47.397
But if you
go to the IA,

37:47.399 --> 37:50.700
if you even look
like you're going...

37:52.603 --> 37:54.638
He had a wife,

37:54.640 --> 37:56.306
a kid,

37:56.807 --> 37:58.875
responsibilities.

37:59.777 --> 38:03.580
Take the money.
Do something good with it.

38:06.717 --> 38:08.318
Well...

38:09.920 --> 38:11.688
I tried.

38:12.957 --> 38:15.125
I tried.

38:16.160 --> 38:18.395
But he wouldn't listen.

38:20.831 --> 38:23.366
My boy was stubborn.

38:25.436 --> 38:28.171
My boy was strong.

38:28.173 --> 38:31.775
And he was gonna
get himself killed.

38:32.176 --> 38:35.412
So I told him...

38:35.913 --> 38:39.349
I told him I did it, too,

38:39.351 --> 38:41.818
that I was like Hoffman,
getting by,

38:41.820 --> 38:44.954
and that's what you
heard that night...

38:44.956 --> 38:45.755
Me talking him down,

38:45.757 --> 38:50.060
him kicking and screaming
until the fight
went out of him.

38:50.062 --> 38:53.163
He put me up
on a pedestal...

38:58.035 --> 39:00.503
And I had to show him

39:00.505 --> 39:04.808
that I was down in the gutter
with the rest of them.

39:08.646 --> 39:10.613
Broke my boy.

39:13.050 --> 39:16.019
I broke my boy.

39:18.556 --> 39:20.824
He went to Hoffman,
he took the money,

39:20.826 --> 39:21.925
but he hesitated.

39:21.927 --> 39:26.129
Even looking like
you're doing the right
thing to those two

39:26.131 --> 39:27.964
meant that he
wasn't solid,

39:27.966 --> 39:31.067
that he couldn't
be trusted.

39:35.539 --> 39:38.441
I got Matty
to take the money.

39:41.946 --> 39:45.215
And they killed him
two days later.

39:49.388 --> 39:53.857
He was the strongest
person that I ever knew.

39:53.859 --> 39:59.129
He'd have never done it,
not even to save himself.

40:00.131 --> 40:02.932
I was the only one...

40:03.334 --> 40:05.335
I was the only one
that could get him

40:05.337 --> 40:08.738
to debase himself
like that.

40:12.577 --> 40:14.844
And it was for nothing.

40:16.814 --> 40:19.215
I made him lesser.

40:20.818 --> 40:23.253
I made him like me.

40:27.691 --> 40:31.194
And the bastards
killed him anyway.

40:50.347 --> 40:53.082
Hoffman and Fensky...

40:55.619 --> 40:58.455
If they killed Matty...

40:59.824 --> 41:02.192
Who killed them?

41:03.360 --> 41:05.562
Pop...

41:05.729 --> 41:07.764
What happened?

41:12.069 --> 41:14.304
You know what happened.

41:16.474 --> 41:19.075
The question is...

41:21.912 --> 41:24.347
Can you live with it?
